---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Ledger from '../components/Ledger.astro';
import { LARMAC_IPM_NOTICES_URL } from '../site.config';

const knowItems = [
  'Self-reported Ewing sarcoma diagnoses in Ladera Ranch children across 2007, 2013, 2017, 2021, 2022, 2023, and 2024',
  'Additional self-reported cancer cases among Ladera Ranch residents and pets',
  'Regular pesticide, herbicide, and rodenticide applications in common areas, documented in LARMAC notices',
  'CUSD records show the product Cheetah Pro (glufosinate-ammonium) was applied at several Ladera Ranch school sites in 2026',
  'A California Cancer Registry analysis was formally requested in May 2026; results are pending',
  'On July 8, 2026, LARMAC agreed to form a resident advisory committee on Integrated Pest Management',
];

const dontKnowItems = [
  'Whether cancer rates in Ladera Ranch exceed state baselines',
  'What caused any individual case, including the ones reported here',
  'Whether any environmental factor (pesticides, herbicides, rodenticides, water, or something else) is involved',
  'Whether the number or timing of cases reported here is statistically unusual for a community this size',
];

const timeline = [
  {
    when: 'May 2026',
    what: 'Requested a formal analysis from the California Cancer Registry',
    detail: 'Result: pending. We will publish whatever the registry finds.',
  },
  {
    when: 'May–June 2026',
    what: 'Filed public records requests with LARMAC and CUSD',
    detail: 'Requesting pesticide, herbicide, and rodenticide application records for common areas and school sites.',
  },
  {
    when: 'July 8, 2026',
    what: 'Raised these questions at the LARMAC board meeting',
    detail: 'A constructive conversation with the board, who are resident volunteers like us.',
  },
  {
    when: 'Ongoing',
    what: 'Resident advisory committee on Integrated Pest Management is forming',
    detail: 'See News & Updates for how to get involved as it stands up.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What We Know"
  description="An honest ledger of what Ladera Health Watch does and does not know about self-reported cancer cases and environmental records in Ladera Ranch."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 pb-4 pt-10 sm:pt-14">
    <p class="font-display text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gold-700">
      The full picture
    </p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-oak-900 sm:text-5xl">
      What we know. What we don't.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      We are asking reasonable questions and requesting reasonable changes, not making claims we
      can't support. This page lays out, as plainly as we can, the difference between what has
      been documented and what remains genuinely unknown.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-6">
    <Ledger knowItems={knowItems} dontKnowItems={dontKnowItems} />
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-10">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-oak-900">Timeline of the effort</h2>
    <ol class="mt-6 space-y-6 border-l-2 border-sage-300 pl-6">
      {timeline.map((step) => (
        <li class="relative">
          <span
            class="absolute -left-[1.65rem] mt-1.5 block h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-gold-600"
            aria-hidden="true"
          ></span>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sage-500">{step.when}</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-oak-900">{step.what}</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">{step.detail}</p>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-10">
    <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-oak-900">A note on environmental cause</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
        There is no known environmental cause of Ewing sarcoma. Several experts have told us this
        is worth looking into, and that environmental records, especially water and
        pesticide/herbicide use, are the practical place to start. That's why our records
        requests focus there. It is not a claim that any product or practice has caused any
        cancer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="pesticide-notices" class="mx-auto max-w-4xl scroll-mt-20 px-5 py-10">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-oak-900">Reading pesticide notices</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      LARMAC posts notices before applying pesticides, herbicides, and rodenticides in common
      areas. Here's a plain-language guide to what those notices say, so residents can read them
      with confidence. This isn't a claim that any specific product is dangerous.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sage-500">Product</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
          The brand name and usually the active ingredient. Look up either one; see below.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sage-500">Location</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
          Which common area or landscaping zone the application covers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-oak-700/25 bg-paper-50 p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sage-500">Date</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
          The application date, and often a posting date in advance of it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      Many notices mention a <em>"restricted entry interval"</em> (REI): standard, required label
      language stating how long to wait after an application before re-entering the treated area
      without protective equipment. It's routine on pesticide labels generally, not something
      specific to Ladera Ranch or to any one incident.
    </p>

    <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-oak-900">Official notices:</strong> LARMAC posts its IPM (Integrated
        Pest Management) and spray notices at
        <a href={LARMAC_IPM_NOTICES_URL} class="text-fog-700 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          laderalife.com ↗
        </a>.
        <span class="text-sm text-sage-500">(TODO: confirm this is the current path.)</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-oak-900">Product labels and safety data sheets:</strong> search the
        product name plus "safety data sheet" (SDS, or older, "MSDS") for the manufacturer's own
        label, ingredients, and handling guidance.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-10">
    <div class="border border-sage-300 bg-paper-50 p-6">
      <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-oak-900">Community Map</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base leading-relaxed text-oak-700">
        We're building a map showing aggregated, anonymized case counts, never individual homes
        or identifiable cases. An aggregate map is
        <a href="/map/" class="text-fog-700 underline">coming soon</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
